The economic environment of a business is handled from the micro, as well as macro economical aspect. The sub-topics are the general macro economical, monetary and fiscal environment. The regional and local aspects of the environment, and the national regulation of the competition conditions and rules.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Explore external environment of enterprise and its development.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student knows different theoretical and empirical models of business environment, comprehends role of institutions in economic development, knows estimations given for Estonia (strengths and weaknesses), can analyze macro- and microeconomic policies which design business environment in Estonia and European Union.
